MCP runtime wiring: connect_all + tool injection + encryption removal

### Fixed
- McpRuntimeClient.connect_all() now called via FastAPI lifespan on startup
- MCP tools from connected servers injected into ToolRegistry via McpToolAdapter
- Config changes (add/update/delete) auto-trigger tool refresh

### Added
- core/mcp_server/tool_adapter.py: McpToolAdapter wraps MCP tools as BaseTool

### Changed
- core/mcp_server/client.py: list_tools(), call_tool(), list_all_tools()
- core/main.py: lifespan handler, _connect_mcp_servers(), _disconnect_mcp_servers(), _refresh_mcp_tools()
- core/tools/mcp_tools.py: set_refresh_callback with auto-trigger on config changes

### Removed
- core/mcp_server/manager.py: all encryption code (_get_encryption_key, _encrypt_field,
  _decrypt_field, _encrypt_sensitive_fields, _decrypt_sensitive_fields, _is_sensitive_key,
  _SENSITIVE_KEYWORDS, auto-encrypt migration in _ensure_loaded)

### .gitignore
- Added exclusions for runtime data, test output, docs, scripts, config, etc.
- venv/ tracked (user preference)

### Tests
- tests/test_mcp_connect_e2e.py: 32 tests covering full wiring pipeline
- tests/test_mcp_server.py: 20 tests (removed TestEncryption class)
